Ashekri and Dole Machina wards in Geidam and Machina Local Government Areas of Yobe state have become the latest communities hit by flood disaster in the State. Data released by the Yobe State Emergency Management Agency, (SEMA), on Saturday, showed that 157 households in Geidam and 161 households in Machina LGs were affected by the flood which was accompanied by a violent windstorm. The State Humanitarian Agency, through its Executive Secretary, Dr. Mohammed Goje noted that even though no life was lost, a 25-year-old woman from Geidam, who sustained injury due to building collapse, with her infant, were evacuated and admitted at the State Specialist Hospital in Damaturu where they are currently receiving free medical treatment. According to him, the State Governor, Mai Mala Buni has directed that all victims be supported within available resources to cushion their hardships. The SEMA tasked communities, as well as religious leaders to intensify calls on members of the public to support remedial measures by clearing drainages, avoid building on waterways and encourage tree planting to mitigate the impact of flooding. Checks by DAILY POST showed that, so far, flood disaster has hit five out of the 17 local government areas of Yobe State. Many more are expected to experience flooding as predicted by the Nigerian Meteorological Agency, (NiMet).